            "arguments": "{\"userQuestion\":\"Show weather events in Texas\"}",
            "output": "Here are some recent weather events in Texas:\n\n- High Wind (12/30/2007): Peak gust of 71 mph at McDonald Observatory in the Davis Mountains. High winds continued into the early morning. No reported damage or injuries.\n- High Wind (12/27/2007): 60 mph winds broke windows and knocked down power poles in El Paso. No reported injuries or deaths.\n- Heavy Snow (12/27/2007): Four inches of snow reported near Perryton and at Spearman. No reported impacts.\n- Winter Weather (12/27/2007): One inch of snow led to icy conditions near the Canadian River Bridge on US 287, resulting in an accident with one fatality and three injuries.\n- Tornado (12/27/2007): Tornado near Slaton, visible on media, no damage reported. Another tornado north of Lubbock: visible, no damage.\n- Strong Wind (12/27/2007): Winds caused a metal shed failure in Lubbock, resulting in minor damage ($2,000).\n- Winter Weather (12/22/2007): Snow and blowing snow near Amarillo contributed to a pileup on I-40, with one fatality, 21 hospitalized, and over 100 minor injuries.\n\nIf you need more details or information on specific events, please let me know!\n",
