            "role": "assistant",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Here are some recent weather events in Texas:\n\n1. **High Wind (12/30/2007)**: Peak gust of 71 mph occurred at McDonald Observatory in the Davis Mountains. The winds continued into the early morning with no reported damage or injuries.\n\n2. **High Wind (12/27/2007)**: Winds of 60 mph broke windows and knocked down power poles in El Paso, Texas. No injuries or deaths were reported.\n\n3. **Heavy Snow (12/27/2007)**: Four inches of snow were recorded near Perryton and Spearman. There were no reported impacts.\n\n4. **Winter Weather (12/27/2007)**: Icy conditions resulted in a traffic accident near the Canadian River Bridge on US 287, with one fatality and three injuries reported.\n\n5. **Tornado (12/27/2007)**: \n   - A tornado near Slaton was visible on media but caused no damage.\n   - Another tornado north of Lubbock was visibly confirmed, but no damage was reported.\n\n6. **Strong Wind (12/27/2007)**: In Lubbock, high winds caused the failure of a metal shed, resulting in minor property damage estimated at $2,000.\n\n7. **Winter Weather (12/22/2007)**: Snow and blowing snow near Amarillo contributed to a pileup on Interstate 40. This caused one fatality, 21 hospitalizations, and over 100 people suffering minor injuries.\n\nLet me know if you’d like more information on any of these events!",
